        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @Sausageberg- Firstly, this game isn't as important as the Southampton game because, with all respect to West Ham, they won't be able to last the distance and will finish in the bottom half whereas it's clear Southampton will be challenging for Europe, possibly even the top 4 if they strengthen in January. If it's a choice of resting players for this game so they have more energy for the Southampton game or vice versa, it's clear which option should be chosen. As for Szczesny, I'm not talking about his physical fitness but he's someone who has chronic concentration problems so whenever you can give him a mental rest, you have to take it. Martinez might be our 3rd choice keeper when all 3 are fit but Ospina still isn't 100% so Martinez is our 2nd choice keeper by default.
